The paper discusses the development of intelligent radio technology for spectrum management, which involves the integration of signal processing, machine learning, and contextual adaptation. This topic is closely related to the field of networked systems and communication technologies, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a new intelligent radio architecture that utilizes machine learning techniques for spectrum sensing, coverage prediction, and channel selection, which aligns with the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the challenges and opportunities for spectrum management in the context of Industry 4.0, which relates to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
